3 WHEREAS, Mrs. Prevost displayed a measure of courage that reshaped the
4 trajectory of American democracy; her courage enforced the constitution, her faith advanced
5 justice, and her sacrifice expanded opportunity for Black Americans; and
6 WHEREAS, Dorothy Prevost is a civil rights and American icon whose inspiring
7 legacy is forever preserved in the country's history.
8 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
9 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby express heartfelt condolences on the death of
10 Dorothy Prevost, the last living matriarch of the 1960 New Orleans public school
11 desegregation movement, and does hereby encourage all Louisianians to honor her inspiring
12 life and legacy of courage.
